[metadata]
Name=Spirit Link Pinger
Description=WU deck stuffed with Prodigal Sorcerer (the classic {T}: deal 1 damage to any target pinger) and Spirit Link so random-vs-random play enchants a pinger and activates its NON-combat damage ability. Used by the native-vs-WASM equivalence sweep to prove that Spirit Link's "whenever enchanted creature deals damage, you gain that much life" trigger firing on NON-combat damage (mtg-r9po1, CR 119.3) replays BYTE-IDENTICALLY across compile targets. The lifegain amount is a pure function of the public damage event, so no hidden information leaks across the engine boundary. Mirror match maximizes the chance both players get a pinger enchanted and ping each turn.

[Main]
10 Plains
10 Island
12 Prodigal Sorcerer
12 Spirit Link
4 Sol Ring
4 Mox Pearl
4 Mox Sapphire
